A coldStart trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is reinitializing itself such that the agent's configuration or the protocol entity implementation may be altered.
A warmStart trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is reinitializing itself such that neither the agent configuration nor the protocol entity implementation is altered.

A linkDown trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role,has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links is about to enter the down state from some other state

A linkUp trap signifies that the SNMPv2 entity, acting in an agent role,has detected that the ifOperStatus object for one of its communication links is about to enter the down state from some other state
An authenticationFailure trap signifies that the sending protocol entity is the addressee of a protocol message that is not properly authenticated.
An egpNeighborLoss trap signifies that an EGP neighbor for whom the sending protocol entity was an EGP peer has been marked down and the peer relationship no longer obtains.
